service:
The Amazon Web Services Deadline Cloud API provides infrastructure and centralized management for your projects. Use the Deadline Cloud API to onboard users, assign projects, and attach permissions specific to their job function.

With Deadline Cloud, content production teams can deploy resources for their workforce securely in the cloud, reducing the costs of added physical infrastructure. Keep your content production operations secure, while allowing your contributors to access the tools they need, such as scalable high-speed storage, licenses, and cost management services.

operations.AssociateMemberToFarm: Assigns a farm membership level to a member.
operations.AssociateMemberToFleet: Assigns a fleet membership level to a member.
operations.AssociateMemberToJob: Assigns a job membership level to a member
operations.AssociateMemberToQueue: Assigns a queue membership level to a member
operations.AssumeFleetRoleForRead: Get Amazon Web Services credentials from the fleet role. The IAM permissions of the credentials are scoped down to have read-only access.
operations.AssumeFleetRoleForWorker: Get credentials from the fleet role for a worker.
operations.AssumeQueueRoleForRead: Gets Amazon Web Services credentials from the queue role. The IAM permissions of the credentials are scoped down to have read-only access.
operations.AssumeQueueRoleForUser: Allows a user to assume a role for a queue.
operations.AssumeQueueRoleForWorker: Allows a worker to assume a queue role.
operations.BatchGetJobEntity: Get batched job details for a worker.
operations.CopyJobTemplate: Copies a job template to an Amazon S3 bucket.
operations.CreateBudget: Creates a budget to set spending thresholds for your rendering activity.
operations.CreateFarm: Creates a farm to allow space for queues and fleets. Farms are the space where the components of your renders gather and are pieced together in the cloud. Farms contain budgets and allow you to enforce permissions. Deadline Cloud farms are a useful container for large projects.
operations.CreateFleet: Creates a fleet. Fleets gather information relating to compute, or capacity, for renders within your farms. You can choose to manage your own capacity or opt to have fleets fully managed by Deadline Cloud.
operations.CreateJob: Creates a job. A job is a render submission submitted by a user. It contains specific job properties outlined as steps and tasks.
operations.CreateLicenseEndpoint: Creates a license endpoint to integrate your various licensed software used for rendering on Deadline Cloud.
operations.CreateMonitor: Creates an Amazon Web Services Deadline Cloud monitor that you can use to view your farms, queues, and fleets. After you submit a job, you can track the progress of the tasks and steps that make up the job, and then download the job's results.
operations.CreateQueue: Creates a queue to coordinate the order in which jobs run on a farm. A queue can also specify where to pull resources and indicate where to output completed jobs.
operations.CreateQueueEnvironment: Creates an environment for a queue that defines how jobs in the queue run.
operations.CreateQueueFleetAssociation: Creates an association between a queue and a fleet.
operations.CreateStorageProfile: Creates a storage profile that specifies the operating system, file type, and file location of resources used on a farm.
operations.CreateWorker: Creates a worker. A worker tells your instance how much processing power (vCPU), and memory (GiB) you’ll need to assemble the digital assets held within a particular instance. You can specify certain instance types to use, or let the worker know which instances types to exclude.
operations.DeleteMonitor: Removes a Deadline Cloud monitor. After you delete a monitor, you can create a new one and attach farms to the monitor.
operations.GetSessionAction: Gets a session action for the job.
operations.GetSessionsStatisticsAggregation: Gets a set of statistics for queues or farms. Before you can call the GetSessionStatisticsAggregation operation, you must first call the StartSessionsStatisticsAggregation operation. Statistics are available for 1 hour after you call the StartSessionsStatisticsAggregation operation.
operations.GetStorageProfileForQueue: Gets a storage profile for a queue.
operations.ListAvailableMeteredProducts: A list of the available metered products.
operations.ListBudgets: A list of budgets in a farm.
operations.ListMonitors: Gets a list of your monitors in Deadline Cloud.
operations.StartSessionsStatisticsAggregation: Starts an asynchronous request for getting aggregated statistics about queues and farms. Get the statistics using the GetSessionsStatisticsAggregation operation. Statistics are available for 1 hour after you call the StartSessionsStatisticsAggregation operation.
operations.TagResource: Tags a resource using the resource's ARN and desired tags.
operations.UntagResource: Removes a tag from a resource using the resource's ARN and tag to remove.
operations.UpdateBudget: Updates a budget that sets spending thresholds for rendering activity.
operations.UpdateMonitor: Modifies the settings for a Deadline Cloud monitor. You can modify one or all of the settings when you call UpdateMonitor.
